<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1410,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1555,1581]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronym in honor of Carlos Perafán, for his contributions to the taxonomic studies of Neotropical Mygalomorphae spiders.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1410,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1626,1652]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[433,621,1627,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perafani" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[433,621,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Patrera perafani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[628,690,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[628,690,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[901,997,1627,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borjai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[901,997,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. borjai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1066,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1004,1066,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1121,1276,1627,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quillacinga" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1121,1276,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. quillacinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1282,1345,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1282,1345,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having a long embolus devoid of basal projections or denticles (
<figureCitation box="[833,924,1663,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-27@14.[151,1436,181,1917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 6A–G. Patrera borjai n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-6074): A habitus, dorsal view; B left palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Female (IBSP 237017): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, B: 2mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468395/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 6C</figureCitation>
̅E, 11C̅E), but differs by having longer and thin retrolateral tibial apophysis, slightly curved and apically sharp (wider and shorter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1149,1304,1699,1725]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quillacinga">
<emphasis box="[1149,1304,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. quillacinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shorter and apically truncated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[432,527,1735,1761]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borjai">
<emphasis box="[432,527,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. borjai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[551,637,1735,1763]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-57@21.[151,1435,273,1854]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 9A–G. Patrera perafani n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10602): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-5429): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468401/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
̅E). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="F. O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[994,1083,1735,1761]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[994,1083,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1136,1230,1735,1761]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1136,1230,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1236,1298,1735,1761]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1236,1298,1735,1761]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the short and wide lateral borders, short copulatory ducts, and large spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1092,1771,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-27@18.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8A–G. Patrera dimar n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10634): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-10635): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C: 1mm; D–E 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468399/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
̅G; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[1144,1379,1771,1797]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref40616" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revis &quot; o de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regi &quot; o neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187." type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit 1997: 147</bibRefCitation>
, figs 55̅56), but can be diagnosed by the triangular, thin hood and rounded, small spermathecae (larger in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="F. O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1298,1388,1807,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[1298,1388,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,246,1843,1869]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar">
<emphasis box="[151,246,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[270,355,1843,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-57@21.[151,1435,273,1854]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 9A–G. Patrera perafani n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10602): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-5429): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468401/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
̅G).
</paragraph>
